content: This app is exactly what I was looking for. It is based on the reddit recommended body weight fitness routine and makes it completely customizable and also allows you to create your own progressions and workouts

The developer posted about this app on reddit bodyweight fitness community so gave the free version a try. Initially it was not very intuitive but once you get the hang of it it's very easy to use and minimalist app. So I bought the pro version. It uses the updated bodyweight recommended routine from reddit. Couple of suggestions - 1. add feature to let non-US users change date format to dd/mm/yy instead of US style. 2. Videos for advanced exercises or feature to let user link YouTube videos
Nice app and very easy to customize workouts.

I've tried three or four different work out apps and this one is probably my favorite. The default workout follows reddits bodyweight fitness subreddit's recommended routine. It's easy to modify the workouts to a degree, but be warned that the number of exercises in it's library isn't the most extensive, so if you like getting really creative it might not be the best option for you. For me though this app is excellent, and I'd recommend it to anyone to try.

Great app. I've used it for the RR the past several months with great success. I have since moved on to Antranik's intermediate PPL routine (rings based) and bought the Pro version to be able to enter them as custom workouts and to support the devs work. Future feature request: ability to back up progress and custom routines to Google Drive

Pretty fantastic. It does what it sets out to do, though very little past that. I wish the individual exercises had more detailed instructions to help me with form, but it's nothing a little googling can't fix

Loved the free version so I bought the pro! Only thing I noticed that's missing is on the skill days after the 'skill work' the mobility work only has the pancake mobility. It's missing the option to change it out for general mobility, overhead mobility, and front splits. Would love to have this added! Still a great app and definitely worth the purchase!
replyContent: Thanks a lot. Good point. I'll try to cover it in the future.

content: It's probably not a big priority but i wouldn't mind seeing Google fit integration. It's a great app though, not often you find something perfectly suited to what you need.

Really good app. Just bought the pro version after using the free one for a while, to support further development. A few minor complains: - It would be absolutely great, if the timer and countdown sounds could get played as alarm instead of media sounds. I would love to have my phone on DnD while training - Deadbug gif doesn't play - Google Fit sync would be great - Sometimes rest countdown stops if app is in background

This app has made a huge difference to my routine, progress and motivation. It's invaluable to me now. I'd love it if i could add my own notes to the records of my progress, so i can keep track of changes made to my form or minor alterations to the exercises i'm performing. Being able to make some exercises weighted would help as well.

solid app and no real problems over the multiple months I have used it.. one thing I would like to see is a graph feature. Also, I rebooted my phone and when I reinstalled the app all my workout history was gone. Another thing that has happened to me a couple times is after watching one of the videos I accidently push the back button to many times and it locks my workout so I have to start a new session to finish, would be nice to keep a workout open to edits for longer.
would be good to see alternative progression videos, at least as a beginner

The application is much better after adding support the creation of its own exercises. But there are still missing two small possibilities: - changes in exercise hold time, since it is not always possible to keep an element for a given time. - You should also add the ability to add a completed item with a weight of 0 kg. or with an alias 'BW' (with own Body Weight)
replyContent: Thanks. I'm currently working on this feature. It will be finished soon.

content: Great app for bodyweight fitness beginners!
Excellent! I use this every workout. Love the option to create my own workouts. I look forward to seeing creation of my own exercises or better stats.
replyContent: Thank you very much. As long as you can not create your own exercises, maybe you cann tell me which exercises you are missing and I will add it to the app.

content: I bought this app to show my support!
